---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LegalArticle from "../components/LegalArticle.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use - Moss"
  description="Terms of Use for the Moss travel companion app."
  bodyClass="legal-page"
>
  <LegalArticle title="Terms of Use" updated="19 July 2026">
    <p>
      These Terms of Use apply to your use of the Moss iOS app and website. By
      using Moss, you agree to these terms and to Apple's standard End User
      License Agreement (EULA) for apps distributed through the App Store.
    </p>

    <h2>Apple standard EULA</h2>
    <p>
      Moss uses Apple's standard EULA. You can review it at <a
        href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/"
        >apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>Subscriptions</h2>
    <p>
      Moss offers an optional auto-renewable subscription named Supporter
      Monthly. Subscription pricing and duration are shown in the app before
      purchase and are confirmed by Apple's purchase sheet.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Payment is charged to your Apple ID after purchase confirmation.</li>
      <li>
        The subscription renews automatically unless canceled at least 24 hours
        before the end of the current period.
      </li>
      <li>
        Your Apple ID account is charged for renewal within 24 hours before the
        end of the current period.
      </li>
      <li>
        You can manage or cancel your subscription in your App Store account
        settings.
      </li>
      <li>
        Canceling a subscription stops future renewal; it does not remove access
        already paid for during the current period.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Accounts and your content</h2>
    <p>
      You are responsible for keeping your account secure and for the trips,
      places, notes, itinerary items, reminders, and other content you add to
      Moss. Do not upload, enter, or share content that you do not have the
      right to use.
    </p>

    <h2>Free and paid access</h2>
    <p>
      Moss may limit some features for free accounts, including the number of
      trips that can be created. Paid subscription access unlocks the features
      described in the app at the time of purchase.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
      Do not misuse the service, interfere with its operation, attempt
      unauthorized access, reverse engineer protected service components, or use
      Moss to violate laws or the rights of others.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      Moss uses service providers to host and operate the app, plus Apple services
      for App Store purchases and notifications, Sign in with Apple and Google
      Sign-In when selected, and Google Fonts for website typefaces. Your use of
      those services may also be governed by their own terms and policies.
    </p>

    <h2>Service changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may change, suspend, or discontinue features as the app evolves. We
      will not intentionally remove paid access during a paid subscription
      period except where required for security, legal, or platform compliance
      reasons.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms from time to time. When we do, we will revise
      the "Last updated" date above. Continued use of the app after changes take
      effect constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about these terms, contact us at <a
        href="mailto:support@getmoss.app">support@getmoss.app</a
      >.
    </p>
  </LegalArticle>
</BaseLayout>
